1
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:54,920
Xiaoxing.

2
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,440
Stop watching TV.

3
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:59,360
Do your Chinese homework in a while.

4
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:00,680
Got it.

5
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:01,840
Let's go.

6
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,160
Auntie,

7
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,000
let me watch a little longer.

8
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:12,000
I really just want to watch a little longer.

9
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,280
Talking is useless. Let's go.

10
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:13,920
Auntie.

11
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,580
Sis, only you can handle this.

12
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,690
Just like you when you were little.

13
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,760
This poem is a Han Yuefu folk song.

14
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:23,280
'He' means 'how'.

15
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:25,480
'Tiantian' refers to

16
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:27,720
the lush growth of lotus leaves.

17
00:01:28,039 --> 00:01:29,500
I know what you're saying.

18
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:33,240
But the teacher asked us to write a 100-word reflection.

19
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,970
And I can't write a single word.

20
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:37,000
Then let's imagine

21
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:40,000
what kind of person would write this poem.

22
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:42,210
'Lotus can be picked in Jiangnan.'

23
00:01:42,479 --> 00:01:44,940
So it's the lotus pickers watching the fish.

24
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,800
As for the lotus pickers,

25
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,680
it describes young men and women.

26
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:50,360
And the picking time

27
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:51,759
is right in midsummer.

28
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,450
It's the time when young men and women work together,

29
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:57,840
and express their love for each other.

30
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,600
You know, the 'lian' in lotus

31
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,410
is a homophone for tender love.

32
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,850
It symbolizes romance.

33
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,600
So when he saw the fish

34
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,530
playing around,

35
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,600
he thought of himself

36
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:10,360
picking lotuses and laughing with his beloved.

37
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,440
Got it?

38
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,520
So it's a love poem after all.

39
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,040
That's easy.

40
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,920
I know all about love.

41
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:20,040
What do you know?

42
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,090
Like you and that older guy.

43
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,800
Don't talk nonsense. What older guy?

44
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,600
He walks you home every day.

45
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,130
You pick lotuses together.

46
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,720
Who told you to talk nonsense?

47
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,180
I'm not talking nonsense.

48
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,380
Don't you look at him on your phone every day?

49
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:35,800
Give it back.

50
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,360
No.

51
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,360
Give me my phone.

52
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:37,800
I won't.

53
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,440
Give it back. Give it back.

54
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,079
No.

55
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:40,800
No.

56
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,720
Give it back

57
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,400
to me.

58
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:42,800
No.

59
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:43,890
Hurry up.

60
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,240
Xiaocen, how old are you?

61
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,640
Still playing around with Xiaoxing.

62
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,000
Auntie, my sister picked a lotus.

63
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:48,400
You.

64
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,970
What lotus picking?

65
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,600
Xiaoxing, what did you say?

66
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,460
My sister is teaching me to recite 'Picking Lotus'.

67
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,000
Xiaoxing, have you finished your homework?

68
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,460
Let's go do your homework.

69
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:14,840
Good morning.

70
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,400
Morning.

71
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,100
Let me help you.

72
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:29,800
No need.

73
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,079
It's fine.

74
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,460
What's wrong with you?

75
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,200
Nothing.

76
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:13,520
Nothing?

77
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,400
Why is it that the more I talk to you,

78
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,600
the more you avoid me?

79
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,839
I'm not.

80
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:19,300
You're not?

81
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,079
No.

82
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:22,180
You call this not avoiding me?

83
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,560
I'm not.

84
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:25,720
I'm not avoiding you.

85
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,520
Good morning.

86
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,120
Why are you two crouching so low?

87
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,180
What are you doing?

88
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,040
Nothing.

89
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,200
You guys go ahead and talk.

90
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,330
I'm rooting for you.

91
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,520
In the Mo'e Xiaolu from the late Yuan and early Ming dynasties,

92
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,780
there is such a record.

93
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:47,680
Craftsmen made an adhesive by mixing gluten with lime

94
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,600
to glue those broken ceramics.

95
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,380
What is its disadvantage?

96
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:55,400
It cannot be soaked in water for a long time.

97
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,400
This means it is afraid of water.

98
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,960
Shortly after,

99
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,640
the technique of porcelain riveting appeared.

100
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,600
This small bowl

101
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:06,560
was repaired using the porcelain riveting technique.

102
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,000
The saying, 'Without a diamond drill,

103
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,520
don't take on porcelain work,'

104
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:11,000
refers to this technique.

105
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:11,970
Later on,

106
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:15,280
there emerged a technique that focuses more on artistry

107
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:19,080
and the aesthetics of the objects, known as gold repair.

108
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:20,800
To be exact,

109
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:22,240
the gold repair technique

110
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,640
should actually be called lacquer repair.

111
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:28,300
It involves applying raw lacquer to the broken porcelain pieces,

112
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,480
and then bonding them together.

113
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,680
Then on the surface of the object,

114
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,640
gold powder or gold leaf is applied

115
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,960
to form this appearance.

116
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:40,320
What's wrong?

117
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,610
Xu Xiao asked me to go to Taoxichuan this weekend.

118
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,360
Don't overthink it.

119
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,200
He usually comes to me

120
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,530
to talk about business.

121
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:54,800
What else did you expect?

122
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,040
Then go with me this weekend.

123
00:05:59,280 --> 00:05:59,800
Sorry.

124
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,640
I have plans this weekend.

125
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,720
Is it too deliberate?

126
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,200
Xiaocen.

127
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:45,960
Xu Xiao.

128
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,080
Why did you ask me out to Taoxichuan?

129
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,240
Didn't I tell you?

130
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,360
There's a youth creative market here on weekends.

131
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,280
Many young artists will set up stalls here.

132
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,280
So I wanted to ask you to come and see.

133
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:01,600
I see.

134
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,120
Yeah.

135
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,460
Isn't it interesting?

136
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,360
Let's go then.

137
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:08,800
Okay.

138
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,040
Come on, take a look.

139
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,160
Imitation Ru ware.

140
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:17,000
Imitation Ru ware, one of the five great kilns of the Southern Song Dynasty.

141
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,480
Come and see.

142
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,000
Our main product is the Flora Cup.

143
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,280
All underglaze color.

144
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,320
Safe, hygienic, and durable.

145
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:23,980
Take a look.

146
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,500
How much is this, boss?

147
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,920
Does it have a theme?

148
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,900
The theme of this porcelain piece

149
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,640
is rebirth and repair.

150
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:38,960
Boss, how much is this?

151
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,840
Two hundred and eighty.

152
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,440
Two hundred and eighty, huh.

153
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,480
These are works of art restored from ceramics.

154
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,170
These works of yours

155
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,920
are not restoration.

156
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,080
Your works

157
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,360
are just piecing together broken porcelain shards.

158
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:56,690
They should be considered cultural and creative products.

159
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,210
Kid, are you buying something?

160
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:02,880
Excuse me.

161
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,040
Stop right there.

162
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:08,640
What's wrong?

163
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,730
Come, come here.

164
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,810
Take a look at our works.

165
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:15,120
Isn't our work pieced together?

166
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,640
Hasn't it been brought back to life?

167
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,600
Then how does it not count as restoration?

168
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,330
First of all,

169
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,640
restoration is a very rigorous matter.

170
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,840
On these works of yours,

171
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,480
there is still leftover glue.

172
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,080
Moreover,

173
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,680
these are all imitation antique porcelain pieces.

174
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,760
You've been scammed.

175
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,020
Have you seen ancient porcelain shards?

176
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:32,840
Jingjing.

177
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,840
Jingjing.

178
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:34,640
Sorry.

179
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,000
That's just her temper.

180
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,000
She meant no harm.

181
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:42,679
All right.

182
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,720
Everyone has the right to speak.

183
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,560
I'm sorry too.

184
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:48,250
I was a bit reckless with my words just now.

185
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,480
Let's go.

186
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,040
I'm so mad.

187
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,000
It's fine.

188
00:08:59,120 --> 00:08:59,640
Class,

189
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,120
to master porcelain repair,

190
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,040
we must first learn to make staples.

191
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,680
Today,

192
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,240
we'll learn how to make them.

193
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,420
The purpose of the staples

194
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,240
is to bind broken porcelain

195
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,080
tightly together.

196
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,000
As for the staples,

197
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,360
there are traditional shuttle-shaped ones,

198
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:22,000
as well as various decorative styles.

199
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,520
Porcelain repair uses staples to bind broken objects

200
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,240
tightly together.

201
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,480
We call this binding objects with iron.

202
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:34,280
It tightly binds broken porcelain together.

203
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:37,800
This is transforming broken pieces into a whole.

204
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,960
It's mealtime already.

205
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,560
But there isn't a single student from our class in the cafeteria.

206
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,490
What's going on?

207
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,720
Is Mr. Yue's assignment too difficult?

208
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,080
Yeah.

209
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,080
Don't mention it.

210
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,880
He asked us to hammer staples.

211
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,240
My hands are blistered.

212
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,360
We can't eat, Mr. Liang.

213
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,240
But you still have to eat when it's mealtime.

214
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,320
I ruined a bunch of them.

215
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,720
I have to start over again.

216
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,850
Then let me help you.

217
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,680
Mr. Liang.

218
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,040
Did Xu Xiao make these staples?

219
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,820
Mr. Liang, how could you tell?

220
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,440
This kind of technique

221
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,240
isn't something newly learned.

222
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,600
I heard Xu Xiao works at an antique shop.

223
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:01,960
He must be exposed to ceramic mending and kintsugi often.

224
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,240
He's already a master.

225
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,600
So,

226
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,640
the assignment Mr. Yue gave this time

227
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,000
in such a short period,

228
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,920
only Xu Xiao could finish it.

229
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:15,400
Look.

230
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,920
No wonder he looked so familiar.

231
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:18,120
That boy from before.

232
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,320
The one who broke the antique

233
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,920
and then cleared up the misunderstanding.

234
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,930
He's quite popular now.

235
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,400
Got some fame.

236
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,400
I'll be leaving first then.

237
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:32,800
Okay.

238
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,660
I'll finish this up

239
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:35,680
and head back too.

240
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:37,940
Drive safe.

241
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,080
Okay. Bye.

242
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,000
Bye.

243
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,060
You're the girl from the market that day.

244
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,200
Zhao Xiaocen.

245
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:55,960
Hello.

246
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,960
Did you make all these cups?

247
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,340
I didn't make them.

248
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:03,800
I just write on them.

249
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,880
That's also very impressive.

250
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,140
They look really nice.

251
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:07,880
Thank you.

252
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:11,210
By the way, I'm looking for Xu Xiao.

253
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:11,840
Is he here?

254
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:13,680
He's inside.

255
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:14,920
Thank you.

256
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,500
Hello, Xu Xiao.

257
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,160
You are the one from Taoxichuan.

258
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,960
What's up? Anything I can help you with?

259
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,930
I heard from a friend

260
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,320
that you appraise treasures here.

261
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,380
I have something I want you to look at.

262
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:52,560
Okay.

263
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,380
Please have a seat.

264
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,000
This is it.

265
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,410
Why are you back?

266
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,640
I left something behind.

267
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:35,800
It's

268
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,160
at Boss Wang's place.

269
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:44,880
Do you know where

270
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,880
these porcelain pieces were found?

271
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,850
Xianghu Village, Fuliang County.

272
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,000
That explains it.

273
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,840
The pieces I saw at your stall a couple of days ago

274
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:52,900
were probably made

275
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,220
by the same person.

276
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:57,480
I found it.

277
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:58,840
Okay.

278
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:02,880
Drive safe.

279
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,200
Bye,

280
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:03,800
Xiaocen.

281
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,000
You can tell that?

282
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,410
These broken pieces

283
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,520
were obviously picked up

284
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:19,600
from the ceramic dump in Xianghu Village.

285
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,930
They are defective fragments of pottery,

286
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,640
glued together.

287
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,640
It seems like turning waste into treasure,

288
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:26,500
very valuable,

289
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:30,140
but there is no real technique involved.

290
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:32,800
This item

291
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:34,770
is fine to play with,

292
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:36,920
but in my opinion,

293
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,370
it's not worth collecting.

294
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:47,240
Then do you think a work like this

295
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,000
can still be saved?

296
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:53,160
From what I can see right now,

297
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,840
it's about combining more complex techniques

298
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,170
in ceramic restoration

299
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:00,500
with the imagination of the ceramic artist.

300
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,280
What techniques?

301
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:05,760
Like porcelain stapling and Kintsugi.

302
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:07,680
Porcelain stapling can be applied

303
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:08,940
to more complex shapes

304
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,940
to make the work sturdier.

305
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,700
Kintsugi can enhance the artistic value

306
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:16,040
and create more possibilities.

307
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,680
I know a bit about what you're saying.

308
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,600
Were you just doing

309
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,730
porcelain stapling restoration?

310
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:24,680
Yes.

311
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,200
Do you also know Kintsugi

312
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,320
or other cultural relic restoration techniques?

313
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,380
Can you do them all?

314
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,020
I've just done some research on them.

315
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,130
How is it?

316
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,770
My little pavilion has some style, right?

317
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,200
Recently,

318
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,220
our Jingdezhen

319
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,480
will have a large number of tourists coming.

320
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,880
So let's take out these nice-looking, fun,

321
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,960
and reasonably priced little plates and bowls

322
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:53,880
to sell.

323
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,320
You two sit here

324
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,640
and do a good job selling.

325
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,160
Be a good front for the shop,

326
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:58,600
got it?

327
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,000
The girl is pretty, and the boy is handsome.

328
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:07,520
Alright, I won't be an eyesore here.

329
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,440
Don't just focus on romance, you know?

330
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,970
Get this month's sales performance up for me.

331
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:19,200
We used to go to the market,

332
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:20,960
but I didn't expect

333
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:23,620
that we would end up being vendors today.

334
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:29,280
How much for these small cups with characters?

335
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,280
Thirty yuan each.

336
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,850
Do you have the characters 'Zhuge' and 'Ran'?

337
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,240
I don't see them.

338
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,240
Found them. Here.

339
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:39,960
Please wrap them up for me.

340
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:40,800
Okay, thanks.

341
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,500
Found them.

342
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,260
Here you go.

343
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,020
You can scan there.

344
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,600
It's sixty yuan in total.

345
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,320
Thank you.

346
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,290
Okay, take care.

347
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,050
How is it?

348
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:51,360
It doesn't seem too hard, right?

349
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,760
It's quite interesting.

350
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,280
How about

351
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,940
you try it with the next customer?

352
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,530
I'll be right beside you. Don't worry.

353
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,170
You do it.

354
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,119
Feel free to look around.

355
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,560
You're deciding between these two, right?

356
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:21,810
How did you know?

357
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:25,290
For these small animal ornaments,

358
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,280
we have a buy one, get one free offer.

359
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,920
If you like both of them,

360
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,000
you can take them both

361
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,720
for thirty yuan.

362
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,560
Then I'll take both.

363
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,020
Please wrap them up for me.

364
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:33,720
Okay.

365
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:34,440
Okay.

366
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,300
Here you go.

367
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:37,840
Take care.

368
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:38,440
Take care.

369
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:40,960
Relax.

370
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:42,880
You did great.

371
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:46,400
I'm just like this.

372
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,560
Every time I see strangers,

373
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,840
I get nervous easily.

374
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,500
But when you talk to me,

375
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,650
aren't you fine?

376
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,640
Because we're familiar.

377
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:27,920
Look,

378
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:28,800
I told you.

379
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,900
We still need to do mid-to-high-end.

380
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,600
The way you do things,

381
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,720
this time we came to Taoxichuan

382
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,560
and sold the studio's stuff,

383
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,400
but it didn't even cover our travel

384
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,460
and meal expenses.

385
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,290
Once we run this studio and exhibition

386
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,400
properly,

387
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:46,920
and get investments,

388
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,800
I'll open a showroom like this for you

389
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,930
and make you the chief ceramic artist.

390
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:52,250
Let's go.

391
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:53,680
Jingjing,

392
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,100
I have something to discuss with you.

393
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,520
I want to delay

394
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,460
the opening time a bit.

395
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,010
And we also need more hands.

396
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,040
Do you have

397
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,730
any candidates in mind?

398
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,020
Just take your time polishing it.

399
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,580
Sorry to bother you again.

400
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:23,160
I didn't introduce myself last time, did I?

401
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,530
My name is Fang Xiaqing.

402
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,920
The works you saw at Taoxichuan before,

403
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,360
and the one I showed you last time,

404
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:31,660
were all made by me.

405
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,760
So you're here this time to...

406
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:36,360
I

407
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,060
am here to recruit you.

408
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,200
I hope you can join my studio.

409
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:45,320
I'm sorry.

410
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,920
I might be a bit abrupt today.

411
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,360
I wonder if you have time

412
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:50,960
to visit my studio.

413
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:54,240
My partner might be able to explain in more detail.

414
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:01,880
This is it.

415
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:02,860
We're here.

416
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:03,480
Come in.

417
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,400
These two rooms are our studios.

418
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,850
Here is the tearoom,

419
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,860
and inside is the main workspace.

420
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,400
This is our studio,

421
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:23,700
and also the place we rent to live.

422
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:25,140
Come, this way.

423
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,920
This is Tian Yuan, and this is Xiao Yu.

424
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,320
Hello.

425
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,440
They are our roommates,

426
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,100
and also our studio partners.

427
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:35,800
Hello.

428
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:36,400
Hello.

429
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:37,220
We're busy.

430
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,000
Just pretend we've already stood up

431
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,860
and hugged you.

432
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:41,480
Welcome.

433
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,480
You guys go ahead.

434
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:42,840
Okay.

435
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,560
If you want it,

436
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,620
you can note down the artwork number.

437
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:47,880
Then,

438
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,360
you can send me a direct message.

439
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:50,480
Today's live stream

440
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,400
ends here.

441
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,120
Bye-bye.

442
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:55,020
Are you just ending the stream like this?

443
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:57,300
I streamed for an hour,

444
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,860
and had only five viewers.

445
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,120
Let me introduce you.

446
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,080
This is Jingjing,

447
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,140
the boss of Banlan.

448
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:06,820
You've met before.

449
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:07,760
You are...

450
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,800
Xu Xiao.

451
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:11,500
You're the one from Taoxichuan that day.

452
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:12,700
Yes, that's right.

453
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:14,570
Here for a visit?

454
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,080
Yes.

455
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:16,560
Okay, take a look around.

456
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:17,680
Come.

457
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,760
These are the works of Banlan.

458
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:22,720
Look at these flowers.

459
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:25,650
They are scrap pieces I collected from a kiln.

460
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:29,240
I used broken porcelain pieces of different colors and textures

461
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,700
and pieced them together.

462
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,720
Are the basic materials of all your works

463
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,380
discarded porcelain pieces?

464
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,040
Yes.

465
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:40,760
Then why did you think of

466
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,440
using these discarded porcelain pieces?

467
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,570
Because it's cheap.

468
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:44,970
That's true.

469
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:46,530
How is it?

470
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:47,840
After seeing these works,

471
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:48,770
do you like them?

472
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,840
They're quite distinctive.

473
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:57,560
Here.

474
00:21:58,760 --> 00:21:59,600
Thank you.

475
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,520
You haven't answered me yet.

476
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,100
Do you want to work with me?

477
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:10,800
It's okay.

478
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,020
Take your time.

479
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:13,520
Contact me when you've decided.

480
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:13,880
Okay.

481
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:26,000
So what do you think?

482
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,720
This Fang Xiaqing...

483
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:31,760
What

484
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,280
about her?

485
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,020
I criticized her work.

486
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:37,100
Not only was she not angry,

487
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,600
but she also invited me to collaborate.

488
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:41,970
Instead of being a sculpture teacher,

489
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:45,340
she came to Jingdezhen for cultural creations.

490
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:48,320
Actually, I also want to explore

491
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,240
whether artifact restoration can

492
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,900
be combined with ceramic art.

493
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:53,480
Maybe.

494
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,360
What's wrong?

495
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,120
Nothing.

496
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:15,040
I

497
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,400
think Fang Xiaqing's studio is pretty good.
